definition.value: A polyazaalkane comprising undecane with three aza groups placed at the 1-, 6- and 11-positions.
A thioacetic acid that is acetic acid in which the oxygen atom of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a sulfur atom.
A nucleotide sugar used as a donor by glycosyltransferases for the synthesis of sugar chains
A quercetin trissulfate having the three sulfo groups placed at the 3-, 3'- and 7-positions.
A dioxo monocarboxylic acid comprising hexanoic acid with the two oxo groups placed at the 3- and 5-positions.
